# WECARE 3.0: Evidence-Based Caregiver Intervention App

## Overview
WECARE 3.0 is a bilingual (English + Mandarin), mobile-first, evidence-based caregiver intervention app for Chinese-American family caregivers. Participants are enrolled via an offline survey; the research team enters survey data into the admin console and emails each participant a one-time access code. The app delivers a structured 7-week curriculum (6 days/week) with daily sessions and a recurring Voice Journal for participant feedback. Content personalization is rule-based, driven by caregiver profile data collected in the survey.

## Tech Stack

- **Frontend**: React Native (iOS/Android), Expo Managed Workflow, EAS Build for App Store / Play Store submission
- **Navigation**: React Navigation
- **UI/UX**: React Native Paper (bilingual-first design)
- **Backend**: Django REST Framework (Python)
- **Database**: AWS RDS (PostgreSQL) via Django ORM
- **Authentication**: AWS Cognito (user pools with custom attributes: cohort, enrollment_week, caregiver_relationship, patient_status, stress_level)
- **Auth Flow**: One-time participant code validated against DB → Cognito user created → permanent session in device SecureStore (no re-login)
- **Voice Journal Integration**: VJ recording module merged directly into WECARE codebase (no separate app or API dependency)
- **Push Notifications**: Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM) + AWS SNS (daily session reminder at 12pm; 24hr unread reminder; Voice Journal reminder)
- **Transcription**: AWS Transcribe (async, server-side, post-upload — no on-device processing)
- **File Storage**: AWS S3 (audio recordings, curriculum media, PDFs)
- **Admin Console**: Django Admin (web-only, browser-based — no mobile admin in v1)
- **Analytics & Logging**: Basic engagement event tracking in v1 (watch time, replay count, emoji reactions); advanced analytics deferred to v2


## App Flow

### Pre-App: Research Team Setup (Django Admin)
1. Participant fills out an offline survey (language preference, caregiver relationship, care recipient status, etc.)
2. Research team enters survey data into Django Admin: participant name, language (EN or ZH), caregiver relationship, care recipient functional status, cohort assignment
3. Django Admin generates a one-time enrollment code and emails it to the participant
4. Participant receives the email with their code before downloading the app

### 1. Enrollment Screen (one-time, never repeated)
- **Purpose**: Authenticate the participant using their emailed one-time code
- **Elements**:
  - WECARE logo and welcome header
  - Participant code entry field
  - "Enroll" CTA button
- **Behavior**: App sends code to backend → validates against DB → retrieves participant's language from survey data → sets app language automatically → creates Cognito session → stores permanent token in SecureStore
- **Note**: Language is not chosen in-app — it is set from the participant's survey response. No baseline questions are collected in-app.

### 2. Home / Dashboard Screen
- **Purpose**: Central hub with card-based navigation to all core features
- **Elements**:
  - Card: **Daily Session** — opens today's required course
  - Card: **Voice Journal** — opens recording screen
  - Card: **History** — opens full session list
  - Card: **Settings** — opens settings screen
- **Layout**: Card grid; bottom tab bar: Home | History | Voice Journal | Settings

### 3. Daily Session Screen
- **Purpose**: Deliver daily multimedia curriculum content
- **Elements**:
  - Course title, week number, and timestamp
  - Multimedia content area with images and text
  - Media tabs: Video | Audio | Text
  - "Additional Resources" section (collapsible: PDFs, links)
  - Emoji feedback bar
- **Tracking**: Watch time and replay count logged per session

### 4. Voice Journal Screen
- **Purpose**: Collect daily/weekly participant input about the program and their caregiving experience
- **Elements**:
  - Bilingual prompt (EN + ZH)
  - Audio recording interface with timer
  - Submit button + progress indicator (e.g., "Week 2/7")
- **Backend**: Audio uploaded to S3 → AWS Transcribe async pipeline → transcript stored in DB

### 5. History Screen
- **Purpose**: Let participants browse and replay all available sessions
- **Elements**:
  - Full list of all sessions
  - Search bar — search by session title
  - Read/unread state indicator per session
- **Layout**: Top search bar, scrollable session list below

### 6. Settings Screen
- **Purpose**: Account management
- **Elements**:
  - Contact us
  - Delete my data
- **Note**: Language is not changeable in-app — it is set from the participant's survey response and retrieved from the admin console on enrollment.

### 7. Admin Console (Django Admin)
- **Purpose**: Research team interface — participant setup, cohort management, notifications
- **Elements**:
  - Enter survey data per participant (name, language, caregiver relationship, care recipient status, cohort)
  - Generate enrollment codes and trigger email delivery to participants
  - Cohort assignment: Treatment / Control / Waitlist
  - Notification scheduler and sending records log
- **Access**: Web-only (browser-based, no mobile admin)

### Push Notifications
- **Daily at 12pm**: "Your daily WeCare session is ready"
- **Voice Journal reminder**: Sent on scheduled VJ days
